-- For-profit Corinthian Colleges exploring strategic alternatives
-- By Rohit T. K. in Bangalore
-- Tue May 06, 2014 08:28AM EDT
-- None



May 6 (Reuters) - Corinthian Colleges Inc <COCO.O> said it would explore strategic alternatives as student enrollments decline and the company faces potential legal action from U.S. regulators.

The for-profit education company said its board had authorized the retention of an investment bank to explore its options. [ID:nGNXVAMKWa] California-based Corinthian faces potential legal action from U.S. consumer regulators over issues related to student loans. [ID:nL3N0KG4D4] The company also said it was in non-compliance with certain bank debt covenants, but expected a waiver.